    "body": "If `flash-attn` is not installed, vLLM on ROCm (with any attention backend) would [fail with](https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/blob/9db78f34dce03d149f3571d45a2d2f259bdc7d15/vllm/attention/utils/fa_utils.py#L25) `Rocm platform requires upstream flash-attn to be installed` due to the unconditional import of `vllm.attention.utils.fa_utils` in `vllm.v1.spec_decode.eagle` which in turn is unconditionally imported by `vllm.v1.worker.gpu_model_runner`.\nThis PR delays the exception to the point that flash attention is used, allowing to run workflows with different attention backends (e.g. triton attention).\n\n## Purpose\n\n## Test Plan\nOn gfx1151:\n```\npip uninstall flash-attn\n# Uses triton attention by default\nvllm bench throughput --model Qwen/Qwen3-4B-AWQ --input-len 256 --gpu-memory-utilization 0.4\n```\n\n## Test Result\n\nPassed.\n\n---\n\n> [!NOTE]\n> Makes ROCm tolerate missing `flash-attn` by deferring failure until flash attention is actually invoked.\n> \n> - On ROCm, replaces immediate import-time error with a stub `flash_attn_varlen_func` that raises a clear `ImportError` only when called\n> - Leaves CUDA/XPU code paths and flash-attn version logic unchanged\n> \n> <sup>Written by [Cursor Bugbot](https://cursor.com/dashboard?tab=bugbot) for commit 8030f68c1c05ff33033724dfa7cd7af970a8ec73. This will update automatically on new commits. Configure [here](https://cursor.com/dashboard?tab=bugbot).</sup>\n\n---\n\n> [!NOTE]\n> Makes flash-attn optional on ROCm by deferring failure from import time to call time.\n> \n> - On ROCm, replaces immediate import error with a stub `flash_attn_varlen_func` that raises `ImportError` only when invoked\n> - CUDA/XPU code paths and `get_flash_attn_version` behavior remain unchanged (ROCm still returns `None`)\n> \n> <sup>Written by [Cursor Bugbot](https://cursor.com/dashboard?tab=bugbot) for commit 97c2acdd45620fb750cd11d44d10c99b16422199. This will update automatically on new commits. Configure [here](https://cursor.com/dashboard?tab=bugbot).</sup>\n\n---\n\n> [!NOTE]\n> Makes flash-attn optional on ROCm by deferring failure from import to call time.\n> \n> - On ROCm, replaces immediate import-time error with a stub `flash_attn_varlen_func` that raises `ImportError` only when invoked\n> - CUDA/XPU code paths and `get_flash_attn_version` logic remain unchanged (ROCm still returns `None`)\n> \n> <sup>Written by [Cursor Bugbot](https://cursor.com/dashboard?tab=bugbot) for commit a6dcec05841532fb8efa40eb8066b7410211dc85. This will update automatically on new commits. Configure [here](https://cursor.com/dashboard?tab=bugbot).</sup>\n",
